4207
03:28:38.905 --> 03:28:42.225
of different ways, which can create uncertainty

4208
03:28:42.405 --> 03:28:43.785
and uneven outcomes.

4209
03:28:45.495 --> 03:28:48.625
Finally, we recommend maintaining consistency

4210
03:28:48.625 --> 03:28:50.065
between the new legislation

4211
03:28:50.205 --> 03:28:52.705
and existing standards where possible so

4212
03:28:52.705 --> 03:28:54.985
that the overall system remains coherent

4213
03:28:54.985 --> 03:28:58.065
and workable for councils, developers, and communities.

4214
03:29:00.415 --> 03:29:02.755
So in short, we think these bills provide a

4215
03:29:02.755 --> 03:29:03.915
really strong foundation.

4216
03:29:04.975 --> 03:29:08.155
The changes we propose are modest but important.

4217
03:29:08.905 --> 03:29:11.995
They're intended to improve clarity, consistency,

4218
03:29:12.055 --> 03:29:13.955
and practical operability so

4219
03:29:13.955 --> 03:29:17.195
that the planning system can more effectively manage natural

4220
03:29:17.195 --> 03:29:20.395
hazard risk support, safer development over time,

4221
03:29:20.975 --> 03:29:24.595
and reduce avoidable social and fiscal costs in the future.

